{"name":"Devout","type":"background","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>In many campaign settings, there is a culture where religion plays a central role in nearly everything they do. Some with the devout background were raised by priests. Many with the devout background are raised by devout members of a less devout society, or are members of a small sect or cult. </p><p>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.5l8QNlgPDPOHpGID]{Languages}: Common and one other</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.rv19GFzEa0nMTuAF]{Skills}: two of your choice: (Recommended: Insight and Religion)</p><p>Cantrips: Guidance</p><p>Spells: Protection from Evil and Good. You can cast this spell once per long rest without expending a spell slot. If you are a spellcaster, you count this spell as a spell you know and have prepared, and can cast it with a spell slot. This spell is a bonus on top of your normal number of spells known.</p><p>One of:</p><ul><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.nfEDSQG0DMBs7eGp]{Weapons}: @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-mundane-items.qqsRY0HoGdEJ6dZr]{Light Hammer}, @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-mundane-items.wPcrbw6GTNb9ZYvp]{Light Crossbow}, @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-mundane-items.ntmAbPMerRRj93Jy]{Mace}, @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-mundane-items.YeHixhF01JFTKaNf]{Morningstar}, @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-mundane-items.pW1brh2c1mr4LyCq]{Heavy Crossbow}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.SySQiDfSWcSRUCFN]{Tools}: One set of @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.SySQiDfSWcSRUCFN.JournalEntryPage.wuMEnZz82yY02Dok#artists-supplies]{Artist's Supplies} of your choice​​</p></li></ul><p><em>In the world of Elkan, the Solar Hegemony is a predominantly human kingdom ruled by living saints who have ascended and become angels, each embodying one of their revered virtues. The Archangels, the first among the saints, look for mortal paragons of their associated virtues, and raise these mortal paragons as new angels when they die. Further northeast, the gnomish god and Lord of Light, Glanis, walks among his children, encouraging them to take up arms to protect the weak and seek the truth.</em></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"elkan5e.com/ancestrybackground","advancement":[]},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"MKYWAnkTJr0gkDqT":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.hx0vkntvs6F1EZO9"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679939633818,"modifiedTime":1679940737817,"lastModifiedBy":"MKYWAnkTJr0gkDqT"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"3WDfZxtAvGYb60ii"}
{"name":"Arcanist","type":"background","img":"icons/environment/settlement/watchtower-moonlit-blue.webp","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>In most campaign settings, there is at least one culture where magical training is provided to everyone. In many settings, elves are the ones to build these magical 'utopias'. Most with the Arcanist background, however, are mage's apprentices from a young age, learning from local tutors away from mainstream society.</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.5l8QNlgPDPOHpGID]{Languages}: Common and two others (often one @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.5l8QNlgPDPOHpGID.JournalEntryPage.hWc1v85Qrw7KBtif#magical-languages]{Magical Language})</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.rv19GFzEa0nMTuAF]{Skills}: two of your choice: (Recommended: Arcana and Religion)</p><p>Cantrips: Two of your choice from the sorcerer or wizard spell list.</p><p>Spells: Detect Magic. You can cast this spell once per long rest without expending a spell slot. If you are a spellcaster, you count Detect Magic as a spell you know and have prepared, and can cast it with a spell slot. This spell is a bonus on top of your normal number of spells known.</p><p>One of:​</p><ul><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.5l8QNlgPDPOHpGID]{Languages}: One additional language</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.SySQiDfSWcSRUCFN]{Tools}: One crafting tool of your choice</p></li></ul><p><em>In the world of Elkan, the northern realm of Tyopalvka is a no-man's land blasted by magical experiments, monsters, and bandits. While there is no significant central government in Tyopalvka, many unscrupulous wizards have built towers and lairs here to avoid attention. Knowledge of basic magic has slowly bled out of these towers as the wizards take countless apprentices who are later released back into the general population.</em></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","advancement":[]},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"SMzzktN48GxcmwJd":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.S39D7mT7mfEOzpYO"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1668025949384,"modifiedTime":1679939761018,"lastModifiedBy":"MKYWAnkTJr0gkDqT"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"9CMMUPJ2hlqIuQq7"}
{"name":"Cosmopolitan","type":"background","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Characters with the Cosmopolitan background were influenced by many cultures. A cosmopolitan culture is one that includes and encourages members of different world cultures to come together. In most campaign settings, there will be several urban centers where members of any culture are welcome. Most of the time, these cosmopolitan cities are trade hubs, often located along water, and they usually have a large population.</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.5l8QNlgPDPOHpGID]{Languages}: Common and two others (usually @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.5l8QNlgPDPOHpGID.JournalEntryPage.hWc1v85Qrw7KBtif#trade-languages]{Trade Languages})</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.rv19GFzEa0nMTuAF]{Skills}: three of your choice: (Recommended: Persuasion, Insight, and either Deception or Investigation)</p><p>Two of:​</p><ul><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.SySQiDfSWcSRUCFN.JournalEntryPage.wuMEnZz82yY02Dok#musical-instrument]{Musical Instruments}: One of your choice</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.SySQiDfSWcSRUCFN]{Tools}: One tool of your choice</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.SySQiDfSWcSRUCFN.JournalEntryPage.wuMEnZz82yY02Dok#vehicles]{Vehicle Proficiency}: @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.SySQiDfSWcSRUCFN.JournalEntryPage.wuMEnZz82yY02Dok#land]{Land}-OR- @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.SySQiDfSWcSRUCFN.JournalEntryPage.wuMEnZz82yY02Dok#water]{Water} Vehicles</p></li></ul><p><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><em>In the world of Elkan, the country of Karsa is a cosmopolitan place built for the wealthy to partake of extravagant pleasures at the expense of the lower classes and slaves. Outside Karsa, the cities of Mothside City, Ka'uhane, and Batten Cliffs invite anyone to work in their chaotic ports. The Sleeping Towns are watched by gold dragons who prevent anyone from feeling unwelcome. The Borderlands between orc, human, and elven lands are home to varied peoples and never-ending warfare.</em></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"elkan5e.com/ancestrybackground","advancement":[{"_id":"mjsrJs9Yhv6bG5tx","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-background-features.A1lq7R7LbdiZOdvC"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":1,"title":"Feature"}]},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"MKYWAnkTJr0gkDqT":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.hx0vkntvs6F1EZO9"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679939633818,"modifiedTime":1679940444656,"lastModifiedBy":"MKYWAnkTJr0gkDqT"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"c0ERbAE6CVMRiKn5"}
